{
  "stem": "7506.6",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And I remember being there with a lot of other people-- i.e.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Inmates of the camp-- watching and all cheering when this thing went up in flames.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Soon thereafter, and it was in June, there appeared within us, with us, a Dutch Jewish man who was also in the, I would say, group which was called Vrij Nederland.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "There was a brigade in the British Army-- or connected to the British Army-- called Vrij Nederland, which is Free Holland.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Those were Dutch people who had gotten to England and had joined up.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "He came to us and arranged for us to be taken out of Germany.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And we were driven to a small airport, airfield, in a lorry, truck, and we were put on an airplane.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "It was the first time after the war that I was in an airplane, and it was a Army Dakota.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "I remember it so very, very well because it had square windows.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And in the window was a rubber plug.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And when I asked about it, it was so that the soldiers who were being transported in that plane, they could defend the plane by sticking their rifles through the plug, through the hole.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "We were flown, in June '45, two months after the liberation of the camp, approximately two months.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "We were flown to a town in the south of Holland called Eindhoven.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "Eindhoven happens to be the headquarters of the very well-known Philips Company.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "We were received there in a-- like an army-- not an army base, a facility where they had taken over a local school.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And in the schoolrooms, they had made like dormitories.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And we arrived there.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
